{
  "doc_id": "57847",
  "text": "Bile flow, hepatic BA output, and [ 3 H]TC absorption from the intestine are all reduced ϳ50% in fasted rats compared with fed rats [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In the present study, infusion of NT into fasted rats elevated bile flow Х10%, increased BA output Х20%, and enhanced [ 3 H]TC recovery from the intestine approximately twofold. Thus decreased NT secretion during fasting could contribute significantly to the decrements in these parameters. This idea is further supported by the present finding that infusion of the NT antagonist SR-48692 decreased [ 3 H]TC absorption by Х50% and Х25% in the proximal and distal gut, respectively. The finding that SR-48692 infusion decreased the recovery of [ 3 H]TC Х20% when mixed with lipid suggested that NT regulation may also occur during normal digestion.",
